					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ksaid" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1484103); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1484103&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252558" alt="ksaid" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1484103)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ksaid" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1484103); return false;" >ksaid</a></span> <span class="odate time_1356808572 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Dec 2012 19:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1673265">
									

<p>The H-B-F system is good. It's very good. And the humour is pretty good too.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">These&nbsp;things&nbsp;are&nbsp;not&nbsp;so&nbsp;good.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I like it, except for the written out &quot;ess-see-pee&quot;s, which I find jarring when just writing &quot;SCP&quot; would work fine. And there should be a full horizontal line, not just a &quot;—&quot;. And you need to get those ellipses under control. And is it Bailey or Baily? Because it switches halfway through. And there are a few iffy lines. Like the MOM tattoo being a &quot;nice touch&quot;. And &quot;sticking out like a Jack Bright Christmas party&quot;. And that second last line is bordering on awkward, but would work okay if it wasn't for that <em>last</em> line, which is <em>absolutely horrifying</em>.</p>
<p>Because I respect you, and because the Tale is still upvote-worthy, I'm not going to go on a big rant about how terrify strange and wrong and inhuman that last line sounded to me, but I could. <em>The emotion is within me.</em></p>
<p>This comment was quite a barrage of bitching, I know. But those are the only things I don't like about this piece, so over all, positive!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

